25 /**
26 @file sql/filesort.cc
27
28 Standard external sort. We read rows into a buffer until there's no more room.
29 At that point, we use it (using the sorting algorithms from STL), and write it
30 to disk (thus the name “filesort”). When there are no more rows, we merge
31 chunks recursively, seven and seven (although we can go all the way up to 15
32 in the final pass if it helps us do one pass less).
33
34 If all the rows fit in a single chunk, the data never hits disk, but remains
35 in RAM.
36 */
37
